attr.name: compact
attr.description:
This Boolean attribute hints that the list should be rendered in a compact style. The interpretation of this attribute depends on the user agent and it doesn't work in all browsers.
 Usage note:Â Do not use this attribute, as it has been deprecated: the <ul> element should be styled using CSS. To give a similar effect as the compact attribute, the CSS property line-height can be used with a value of 80%.

content: zero or more <li> elements, which in turn often contain nested <ol> or <ul> elements.
omission: None, both the starting and ending tag are mandatory.
parents: Any element that accepts flow content.
